t to add. Should I include `testImplementation jna`? Is that the right choice for a test dependency? It looks like it targets a public API and uses native methods to create a pseudo-terminal and duplicate file descriptors rather than working with a library API. I need to think about the implications of it in a test environment setup — JNA might not work well with Native Image and could fail on metadata. Adding this dependency might not be a good idea.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering JaCoCo agent usage**\\n\\nI'm noting that in the native parent, there's no JaCoCo agent being used. We're still able to spawn a child under the script without it, and the tests are passing with dynamic coverage from the javaTest child, which is great! I'm also wondering if the parent could run `AnsiOutput.setConsoleAvailable(Boolean.TRUE)` to exercise the API in native directly without a pty. That might be an interesting approach to explore!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering code style**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether checkstyle will have an issue with `main` being public in a test. It seems like it won’t really be a problem. I also realize I need to use type annotations for all variables effectively. Maybe I should start writing a test file to ensure I’m following the guidelines properly. It’s always good to stay consistent and clear—getting those details right really matters!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_yCRNFU9GWtOw0qRb4fAAjMmk|fc_034146b97de7a5d6016a252915e21881959ac1806036fd52d8", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/4.0.2/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot/AnsiOutputTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_springframework_boot.spring_boot;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.fail;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.lang.management.ManagementFactory;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.time.Duration;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.springframework.boot.ansi.AnsiColor;\nimport org.springframework.boot.ansi.AnsiOutput;\nimport org.springframework.boot.ansi.AnsiOutput.Enabled;\n\npublic class AnsiOutputTest {\n\n    private static final String CHILD_MODE = \"ansi-output-detect-child\";\n\n    private static final String CHILD_MARKER = \"ansi-detect-child-ok\";\n\n    private static final Duration CHILD_TIMEOUT = Duration.ofSeconds(30);\n\n    @Test\n    void detectModeChecksWhetherTheConsoleIsATerminal() throws Exception {\n        Process process = new ProcessBuilder(scriptCommand()).redirectErrorStream(true).start();\n        boolean exited = process.waitFor(CHILD_TIMEOUT.toSeconds(), TimeUnit.SECONDS);\n        if (!exited) {\n            process.destroyForcibly();\n            fail(\"Timed out waiting for ANSI detection child process\");\n        }\n        String output = new String(process.getInputStream().readAllBytes(), StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n        assertThat(process.exitValue()).as(output).isZero();\n        assertThat(output).contains(CHILD_MARKER);\n    }\n\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        if (args.length != 1 || !CHILD_MODE.equals(args[0])) {\n            throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Expected child mode argument\");\n        }\n        AnsiOutput.setEnabled(Enabled.DETECT);\n        AnsiOutput.setConsoleAvailable(null);\n        String output = AnsiOutput.toString(AnsiColor.GREEN, CHILD_MARKER);\n        if (!output.contains(\"\\u001B[\") || !output.contains(CHILD_MARKER)) {\n            throw new AssertionError(\"ANSI output was not enabled by console terminal detection: \" + output);\n        }\n        System.out.println(CHILD_MARKER);\n    }\n\n    private static List<String> scriptCommand() throws IOException {\n        List<String> javaCommand = new ArrayList<>();\n        javaCommand.add(javaExecutable().toString());\n        javaCommand.addAll(currentJavaAgents());\n        javaCommand.add(\"-cp\");\n        javaCommand.add(System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\"));\n        javaCommand.add(AnsiOutputTest.class.getName());\n        javaCommand.add(CHILD_MODE);\n        String quotedJavaCommand = javaCommand.stream().map(AnsiOutputTest::quoteForShell).collect(Collectors.joining(\" \"));\n        return List.of(\"script\", \"-q\", \"-e\", \"-c\", quotedJavaCommand, \"/dev/null\");\n    }\n\n    private static List<String> currentJavaAgents() {\n        return ManagementFactory.getRuntimeMXBean()\n            .getInputArguments()\n            .stream()\n            .filter((argument) -> argument.startsWith(\"-javaagent:\"))\n            .toList();\n    }\n\n    private static Path javaExecutable() {\n        String executable = System.getProperty(\"os.name\").toLowerCase().contains(\"win\") ? \"java.exe\" : \"java\";\n        return Path.of(System.getProperty(\"java.home\"), \"bin\", executable);\n    }\n\n    private static String quoteForShell(String value) {\n        return \"'\" + value.replace(\"'\", \"'\\\\''\") + \"'\";\n    }\n\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/4.0.2/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot/AnsiOutputTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_springframework_boot.spring_boot;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.fail;\\n\\nimport java.io.IOException;\\nimport java.lang.management.ManagementFactory;\\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\\nimport java.time.Duration;\\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\\nimport java.util.List;\\nimport java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;\\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\\n\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\nimport org.springframework.boot.ansi.AnsiColor;\\nimport org.springframework.boot.ansi.AnsiOutput;\\nimport org.springframework.boot.ansi.AnsiOutput.Enabled;\\n\\npublic class AnsiOutputTest {\\n\\n    private static final String CHILD_MODE = \\\"ansi-output-detect-child\\\";\\n\\n    private static final String CHILD_MARKER = \\\"ansi-detect-child-ok\\\";\\n\\n    private static final Duration CHILD_TIMEOUT = Duration.ofSeconds(30);\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void detectModeChecksWhetherTheConsoleIsATerminal() throws Exception {\\n        Process process = new ProcessBuilder(scriptCommand()).redirectErrorStream(true).start();\\n        boolean exited = process.waitFor(CHILD_TIMEOUT.toSeconds(), TimeUnit.SECONDS);\\n        if (!exited) {\\n            process.destroyForcibly();\\n            fail(\\\"Timed out waiting for ANSI detection child process\\\");\\n        }\\n        String output = new String(process.getInputStream().readAllBytes(), StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\\n        assertThat(process.exitValue()).as(output).isZero();\\n        assertThat(output).contains(CHILD_MARKER);\\n    }\\n\\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\\n        if (args.length != 1 || !CHILD_MODE.equals(args[0])) {\\n            throw new IllegalArgumentException(\\\"Expected child mode argument\\\");\\n        }\\n        AnsiOutput.setEnabled(Enabled.DETECT);\\n        AnsiOutput.setConsoleAvailable(null);\\n        String output = AnsiOutput.toString(AnsiColor.GREEN, CHILD_MARKER);\\n        if (!output.contains(\\\"\\\\u001B[\\\") || !output.contains(CHILD_MARKER)) {\\n            throw new AssertionError(\\\"ANS